1
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:43,168
Ju-ran.

2
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:46,337
Can you hear your Dad's voice now?

3
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:50,383
It was the first thing I ever heard.

4
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:52,677
The sound of warmth.

5
00:01:22,123 --> 00:01:23,583
But the fairy tale

6
00:01:24,709 --> 00:01:26,920
did not have a happy ending.

7
00:01:32,967 --> 00:01:34,511
Help! Over here!

8
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:36,471
Father!

9
00:01:36,554 --> 00:01:39,265
Father!

10
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,088
Run away.

11
00:02:10,171 --> 00:02:11,381
You have to run, Ju-ran.

12
00:02:11,464 --> 00:02:14,092
I will come and find you, so until then,

13
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:17,303
keep yourself hidden
and don't get caught, okay?

14
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:22,934
Go!

15
00:02:36,072 --> 00:02:36,990
Let's go.

16
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:42,370
The children decided
to keep their identities secret

17
00:02:42,453 --> 00:02:44,873
and live in hiding,

18
00:02:45,456 --> 00:02:47,584
waiting for their father
to keep his promise

19
00:02:48,084 --> 00:02:50,336
and return to them.

20
00:02:53,339 --> 00:02:55,341
If you're deaf,
you should at least be sharp.

21
00:02:55,425 --> 00:02:58,094
If you're not sharp,
you could at least be handy.

22
00:02:58,178 --> 00:03:00,054
What a pain!

23
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:04,893
Ju-ran.

24
00:03:17,614 --> 00:03:18,573
It's me, Dad.

25
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:24,037
But the fairy tale did not end there.

26
00:04:01,991 --> 00:04:03,534
Will that be enough?

27
00:04:03,618 --> 00:04:05,745
We have to start somewhere.

28
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:09,791
You kids focus on
finding the Child of Eternity.

29
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:14,003
That's the only thing
that will get us closer

30
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:16,214
to a cure for the side effects.

31
00:04:17,548 --> 00:04:19,425
The children realized

32
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:23,304
that only by finding
the child with the heart of eternity

33
00:04:23,972 --> 00:04:25,723
could all of this

34
00:04:26,307 --> 00:04:29,143
reach a happy ending.

35
00:04:33,731 --> 00:04:36,276
I heard you were released on parole.

36
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,653
A year ago, I believe.

37
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:42,740
I was in there for over 20 years.

38
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:46,703
I'm sure it was
hardly enough time to recall

39
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:48,997
the faces of all the dead children.

40
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:52,041
You never even cared about them
in the first place.

41
00:04:53,543 --> 00:04:55,837
Whatever happened to those children,

42
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:59,424
abandoned, abused,
and wandering listlessly…

43
00:05:00,216 --> 00:05:01,092
You never cared.

44
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,388
My children and I risked everything

45
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:08,683
for that immortality project of yours.

46
00:05:09,183 --> 00:05:12,353
And though, yes,
some sacrifices were made,

47
00:05:13,104 --> 00:05:14,272
I was successful.

48
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:19,485
And yet, to be treated as I was,
like a criminal…

49
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:22,447
I must say, I was hurt.

50
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:24,490
It seems that one of us

51
00:05:25,116 --> 00:05:27,577
has been laboring
under a grave misunderstanding.

52
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:31,622
I didn't fund and support you

53
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:34,292
because I wanted you to succeed.

54
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:36,544
It was for the suffering children.

55
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:40,882
I wonder if believing that
eases your conscience.

56
00:05:45,511 --> 00:05:47,597
I heard that you, Madam King,

57
00:05:48,097 --> 00:05:50,433
took in most of the rescued children.

58
00:05:50,516 --> 00:05:53,019
I found every one of them new families

59
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:55,521
or sent them to study abroad.

60
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:56,439
Why do you ask?

61
00:05:57,774 --> 00:05:58,983
And the Child of Eternity?

62
00:06:04,655 --> 00:06:06,532
So you've seen the Child of Eternity.

63
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:10,161
Where is that child?

64
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:51,786
Let me ask you again.

65
00:06:52,286 --> 00:06:55,039
Where is the Child of Eternity now?

66
00:06:57,583 --> 00:07:01,462
Director Choi already told me everything
with his last breath.

67
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:05,716
That only you, Madam King of Hearty House,

68
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:08,386
know where the Child of Eternity is.

69
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,055
Answer him.

70
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:19,814
That child…

71
00:07:26,237 --> 00:07:27,321
is dead.

72
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,161
What did you say?

73
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:36,539
Dead.

74
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:42,211
The Child of Eternity cannot die.

75
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:56,184
- One more time.
- No, please. Stop.

76
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:58,478
- It's okay.
- I'm scared.

77
00:07:58,561 --> 00:08:01,189
- Please stop.
- Stop it.

78
00:08:01,272 --> 00:08:02,940
No, please stop. I'm scared.

79
00:08:03,024 --> 00:08:04,484
Can't you hear me?

80
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:07,028
- I'm scared. Please, no.
- Hurry.

81
00:08:07,111 --> 00:08:09,822
Please stop. No.

82
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:11,449
Stop it.

83
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:14,243
But immortality doesn't mean

84
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:17,079
immunity to pain.

85
00:08:19,081 --> 00:08:20,291
Every moment,

86
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:23,461
with each and every death.

87
00:08:33,846 --> 00:08:35,014
One more time!

88
00:08:35,097 --> 00:08:36,974
- No, I'm scared!
- It's okay.

89
00:08:37,058 --> 00:08:38,601
Please stop!

90
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:40,019
I said stop!

91
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,438
- Stop it!
- Don't do this.

92
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:48,694
- Please don't do this.
- One more time!

93
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:50,613
Stop!

94
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:54,867
I told you to stop.

95
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:55,993
Stop!

96
00:08:57,328 --> 00:08:58,579
Stop it!

97
00:08:59,205 --> 00:09:00,915
Just stop it!

98
00:09:34,031 --> 00:09:37,034
Ma'am, how much rice should we use?

99
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:41,664
Rice.

100
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:44,458
How much should we soak
for the celebratory rice cakes?

101
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:45,710
Right.

102
00:09:46,502 --> 00:09:48,796
You should soak about three to five mal.

103
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:50,965
So how much exactly?

104
00:09:51,048 --> 00:09:53,092
Three mal or four mal?

105
00:09:53,175 --> 00:09:54,135
Or five mal?

106
00:09:54,635 --> 00:09:58,723
Goodness, what's gotten into you?
You're usually so precise.

107
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:01,058
Hey, Won-ju.

108
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:02,893
Yes?

109
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:05,271
Didn't someone come by just now?

110
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:07,273
Who would've come by?

111
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:09,275
You've been sitting alone the whole time.

112
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:11,277
And how much red bean?

113
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:13,487
Three to five mal of that too?

114
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:15,364
What on earth happened here?

115
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:16,282
Goodness me.

116
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:18,743
Was there an earthquake or something?

117
00:10:18,826 --> 00:10:21,787
Goodness, how completely bizarre.

118
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:25,249
They say the apocalypse is coming.
Maybe the world really is about to end.

119
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,959
Or maybe someone upset the spirits?

120
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:30,087
Why are all these
strange things happening?

121
00:11:11,545 --> 00:11:12,630
Pretty.

122
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:15,841
Should I go to see the Northern Lights?

123
00:11:15,925 --> 00:11:17,593
I heard they're breathtaking.

124
00:11:18,427 --> 00:11:19,345
Hold up.

125
00:11:20,429 --> 00:11:22,848
Couldn't I just teleport there?

126
00:11:23,766 --> 00:11:24,684
No way.

127
00:11:25,351 --> 00:11:27,353
Does that mean I can save on airfares?

128
00:11:28,604 --> 00:11:30,564
Hey, that's pretty awesome!

129
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:32,817
Pretty darn awesome!

130
00:11:43,786 --> 00:11:45,162
ABILITY: GRAVITY
RANK: S

131
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:49,375
ABILITY: HALLUCINATION
GRADE: S

132
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:54,046
ABILITY: BRAINWASHING
RANK: S

133
00:12:48,392 --> 00:12:52,104
THE WONDERFOOLS

134
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:57,985
EPISODE 4
BOON THE KING DUCK VS WUNDERKINDER

135
00:13:22,384 --> 00:13:23,886
Hey, I used to use that thing.

136
00:13:23,969 --> 00:13:27,097
I heard retro is in these days.
Are you into it too?

137
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:30,184
My CD player broke,
and apparently, it's beyond repair.

138
00:13:31,268 --> 00:13:34,480
Mom says I should save for a new one,
but it'll take forever.

139
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:35,481
Hey, wait.

140
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:40,194
How about I get you one for your birthday?

141
00:13:40,778 --> 00:13:42,071
For which birthday?

142
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:45,407
With your allowance,
I'd have to wait until I'm 40 to get it.

143
00:13:47,409 --> 00:13:48,494
Hey, your lunchbox.

144
00:13:57,920 --> 00:13:59,255
Have a good day, sweetie.

145
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:09,473
How's this thing broken exactly?

146
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:19,400
Thousand, ten thousand, hundred thousand…

147
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:24,488
At this price, I couldn't afford it
by her 60th birthday,

148
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:26,448
let alone her 40th.

149
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:35,833
Cheong, you overestimate your old man.

150
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:42,840
Hello?

151
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:46,051
What do you want, Lady Trainwreck?

152
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:49,638
Let's go home, shall we?
Mr. Coo-coo, let's go home.

153
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:52,725
Let's go home. Back to your happy home.

154
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:55,144
Come on, now. Let's go.

155
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:57,646
Let's go.

156
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:10,242
Master!

157
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:34,058
Why are you all…

158
00:15:34,141 --> 00:15:37,019
You asked if we were free on Friday.
And they both were.

159
00:15:37,102 --> 00:15:38,062
All right.

160
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:41,649
How does it feel to have the calvary
on your team, Master?

161
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:45,027
Calvary is where Jesus was crucified.
You mean the cavalry.

162
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:46,612
Get off me.

163
00:15:47,863 --> 00:15:52,117
I must say, you're smarter
than I thought, Mr. Oddball.

164
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:56,497
Who knew you'd give us special training
disguised as Civil Complaints Office work?

165
00:15:57,081 --> 00:15:58,749
We'll be paid for this, right?

166
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:00,459
Special training?

167
00:16:01,835 --> 00:16:03,295
You were totally rad.

168
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:06,674
Lifting things, not to mention my heart,
up and down with one finger!

169
00:16:06,757 --> 00:16:08,092
It was totally--

170
00:16:08,175 --> 00:16:09,051
What are you doing?

171
00:16:09,843 --> 00:16:12,471
As for me,
my heart was brimming with excitement.

172
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:16,266
Like I've become a real civil servant.
And now, you're offering to teach us.

173
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:19,269
Does this mean
we can become as cool as you, Master?

174
00:16:19,353 --> 00:16:21,480
Thank you so much!

175
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:23,273
I will never forget this kindness!

176
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:24,400
You kiss-ass.

177
00:16:24,483 --> 00:16:27,528
Mr. Lee Un-jeong. Very good!
You've finally put together a team?

178
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:29,363
- Two, three!
- Hello!

179
00:16:29,446 --> 00:16:32,533
We're Team Lee Un-jeong
from the Haeseong Civil Complaints Office!

180
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:34,118
At your service!

181
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:37,955
Are you for real?

182
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:40,874
Yes, well…

183
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:44,211
Now, Mr. Lee Un-jeong here
has many shortcomings,

184
00:16:44,294 --> 00:16:46,422
so I'm sure you must be worried, Mr. Yang.

185
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:47,548
But

186
00:16:48,090 --> 00:16:49,341
he's got us now, see?

187
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:55,639
We'll make up for all of his shortcomings,
so don't you worry.

188
00:16:55,723 --> 00:16:56,557
Sure.

189
00:16:57,349 --> 00:17:00,602
Well, then, before my worries
get the better of me…

190
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:01,937
Bring it in.

191
00:17:02,438 --> 00:17:03,772
Let's do this. Good.

192
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:07,317
I'll see you later!

193
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:08,777
Don't you worry!

194
00:17:10,487 --> 00:17:12,698
What's that? The bus? Over here, everyone.

195
00:17:12,781 --> 00:17:14,324
Careful. Watch out for the bus.

196
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:17,077
Okay, keep it coming.

197
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:19,204
Keep coming. That's it.

198
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:23,500
Stop!

199
00:17:23,584 --> 00:17:24,418
All right.

200
00:17:24,918 --> 00:17:26,378
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

201
00:17:27,796 --> 00:17:29,798
Why is the Church
of Eternal Salvation here?

202
00:17:30,382 --> 00:17:33,093
- Why are those cultists here?
- Must be here to recruit us.

203
00:17:34,428 --> 00:17:37,097
Special orders from the mayor,
so no grumbling, okay?

204
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:40,893
Any unnecessary complaining,
and all contract staff could be let go.

205
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:44,229
Why, yes. There you are. Hello.

206
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:45,189
All right.

207
00:17:45,272 --> 00:17:47,816
Today is our street clean-up drive,

208
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:51,653
and members of the Church
of Eternal Salvation will be helping us.

209
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:53,906
Let's welcome them
with a round of applause!

210
00:17:53,989 --> 00:17:55,491
Let's give them a hand!

211
00:17:55,574 --> 00:17:58,494
- Welcome, all! Yes!
- My goodness.

212
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:02,039
Thank you for the warm welcome.

213
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:07,044
When it comes to cleaning up Haeseong,
of course we should help out.

214
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:11,173
Trash should be collected immediately

215
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:14,051
to make the world
a clean and beautiful place.

216
00:18:14,134 --> 00:18:16,637
Yes, you're absolutely right.

217
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:17,554
Collecting?

218
00:18:18,055 --> 00:18:20,599
To cleanse the world
and make it beautiful.

219
00:18:23,268 --> 00:18:25,104
Can we talk for a moment?

220
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:27,940
Come on.

221
00:18:28,941 --> 00:18:31,235
Man, he's got us running
all over the place.

222
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,406
Why are we here?

223
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:43,789
The work's just a front
for us to train here, isn't it?

224
00:18:43,872 --> 00:18:45,499
Of course.

225
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:48,001
We can't do our special training
out in the open.

226
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:49,253
We have to be discreet.

227
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:51,964
No special training.

228
00:18:52,047 --> 00:18:53,841
- Are you kidding?
- What?

229
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:58,887
People only envy and admire people
with abilities like ours

230
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:00,389
in movies.

231
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:03,725
People fear and avoid
those who are different.

232
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:06,353
They are shunned and despised.

233
00:19:06,436 --> 00:19:09,481
People already fear and avoid
Lady Trainwreck here.

234
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:12,651
Should I show you why
right here, right now?

235
00:19:19,408 --> 00:19:20,450
This is it.

236
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:25,581
To live normal lives,
you must control and hide your abilities.

237
00:19:26,248 --> 00:19:27,666
If someone finds out

238
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:31,128
and if that someone
is very intrigued by your abilities,

239
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:34,464
you might never

240
00:19:35,090 --> 00:19:35,966
get to see…

241
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:41,597
your friends, family,
or those you cherish ever again.

242
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:50,772
So we'd really get carted off
if we're caught?

243
00:19:51,565 --> 00:19:53,275
Never get to see them again?

244
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:56,028
No special training would suffice.

245
00:19:56,528 --> 00:19:58,614
Everyone's abilities manifest differently,

246
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,949
so you have to figure out
your own abilities.

247
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:05,245
And how exactly do we figure that out?
That's what we've been asking you.

248
00:20:05,329 --> 00:20:06,330
Repetition.

249
00:20:07,497 --> 00:20:11,627
The only option is repeated practice.
There will be some kind of rule.

250
00:20:12,127 --> 00:20:15,130
Focus on when and in what situations
your abilities manifest.

251
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:20,594
No one leaves this place today
until they've figured something out.

252
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:24,890
Like a fiery test by fire.

253
00:20:24,973 --> 00:20:26,141
Trial by fire.

254
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:28,894
Isn't that a bit too hardcore,
Mr. Oddball?

255
00:20:28,977 --> 00:20:30,646
Can't you go easy on us?

256
00:20:31,146 --> 00:20:33,774
You're not going to lock us up in here

257
00:20:33,857 --> 00:20:35,984
and ship us off in this container,
are you?

258
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:38,570
Come on, who would buy
a shipping container full of us?

259
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:41,114
He's just pushing us so we learn faster.

260
00:20:41,198 --> 00:20:43,533
Understood.
I'll do my best to learn, Master.

261
00:20:43,617 --> 00:20:44,826
Is that what you're doing?

262
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:49,122
Lock the door from the outside.

263
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:51,959
- Okay! Let's give it a try.
- Wait, the door?

264
00:20:52,042 --> 00:20:52,960
Let's do this!

265
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:55,796
Is locking the door really necessary?

266
00:21:00,008 --> 00:21:01,176
This isn't too shabby.

267
00:21:05,555 --> 00:21:06,890
Let's take one of each.

268
00:21:06,974 --> 00:21:08,684
You punk, can't you see I'm hurt?

269
00:21:14,064 --> 00:21:16,525
So we saved them?

270
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:23,740
We're pretty awesome,

271
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:25,367
aren't we?

272
00:21:30,747 --> 00:21:31,623
No.

273
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:33,750
That's not me.

274
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:35,794
I'm just…

275
00:21:40,924 --> 00:21:41,925
Dr. Ha.

276
00:21:52,936 --> 00:21:55,355
His vitals are also declining.

277
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:02,195
Scrap him.

278
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:16,001
We won't end up like that
one day, will we?

279
00:22:19,755 --> 00:22:21,465
If we can't fix the side effects,

280
00:22:22,299 --> 00:22:23,967
we could get deformed like that too.

281
00:22:25,510 --> 00:22:28,722
I just wonder if we'll end up
gasping for air, unable to breathe,

282
00:22:28,805 --> 00:22:31,350
and ultimately scrapped, just like them.

283
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:33,310
Don't you

284
00:22:35,062 --> 00:22:36,313
trust Father?

285
00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:40,776
I do know he's hiding something from us.

286
00:22:41,276 --> 00:22:42,319
Like about 3972.

287
00:22:43,612 --> 00:22:46,281
Father does everything
for a reason, Ho-ran.

288
00:22:46,365 --> 00:22:49,159
Yeah, I'm sure he does.

289
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:52,204
But I'm not sure if that reason

290
00:22:52,704 --> 00:22:55,082
is for our good.

291
00:22:55,165 --> 00:22:58,126
Stop thinking useless thoughts
and go do your job.

292
00:22:58,835 --> 00:23:01,755
Because if we fail to find
the Child of Eternity…

293
00:23:04,383 --> 00:23:07,511
all that awaits us,
Father included, is death.

294
00:23:08,512 --> 00:23:11,056
Okay, I got it.

295
00:24:05,861 --> 00:24:06,862
My goodness!

296
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:12,033
- My congratulations!
- Oh my.

297
00:24:12,117 --> 00:24:13,827
Have a read before you go in!

298
00:24:13,910 --> 00:24:15,662
- Oh my!
- Congratulations!

299
00:24:15,745 --> 00:24:17,581
- Go in now.
- She got a job?

300
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:20,459
- Congratulations!
- Thank you.

301
00:24:22,169 --> 00:24:24,212
So do you think it can be restored?

302
00:24:24,296 --> 00:24:26,381
No, it doesn't seem likely.

303
00:24:27,716 --> 00:24:31,011
It wasn't just overwritten
but completely erased by a magnetic field.

304
00:24:32,387 --> 00:24:35,557
I spent a fortune installing
those security cameras or whatnot,

305
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:36,933
but they're darn useless.

306
00:24:37,017 --> 00:24:39,603
One camera managed to capture something.

307
00:24:39,686 --> 00:24:40,687
What?

308
00:24:43,565 --> 00:24:44,608
The camera out back.

309
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:07,255
What is it?

310
00:25:08,924 --> 00:25:12,594
It's that woman.
The variant 3972 hangs out with.

311
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:19,434
What should we do?

312
00:25:22,103 --> 00:25:22,979
Collect her.

313
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:39,538
If this works, it'll be huge.

314
00:25:39,621 --> 00:25:43,750
The northern lights.
It'd be great if I could really go there.

315
00:25:45,502 --> 00:25:46,545
The northern lights.

316
00:25:47,045 --> 00:25:48,922
How awesome would that be?

317
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:52,217
Let's go. Yeah.

318
00:25:52,968 --> 00:25:53,843
Let's go!

319
00:25:57,013 --> 00:25:58,265
Guess not.

320
00:25:58,348 --> 00:25:59,933
Okay, focus.

321
00:26:02,852 --> 00:26:03,853
And I'm still here.

322
00:26:04,354 --> 00:26:05,605
Okay, focus now.

323
00:26:17,951 --> 00:26:18,785
Did you see that?

324
00:26:18,868 --> 00:26:20,620
What on earth happened

325
00:26:21,454 --> 00:26:22,872
to my Chae-ni just now?

326
00:26:24,082 --> 00:26:25,333
Did she just vanish?

327
00:26:26,876 --> 00:26:29,045
Did you succeed? Where did you go? Norway?

328
00:26:29,129 --> 00:26:30,088
Finland?

329
00:26:30,171 --> 00:26:31,715
Did you really see the aurora?

330
00:26:36,219 --> 00:26:37,053
I did.

331
00:26:37,137 --> 00:26:38,638
AURORA

332
00:26:39,139 --> 00:26:42,809
Put a name tag on my chest…

333
00:26:42,892 --> 00:26:43,935
I'm here, baby.

334
00:26:44,019 --> 00:26:45,145
Cheers!

335
00:26:47,939 --> 00:26:49,524
Deary me. Miss?

336
00:26:50,692 --> 00:26:52,819
No, don't go. Why are you leaving?

337
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,654
Come again tomorrow.

338
00:26:55,155 --> 00:26:56,281
She's cute.

339
00:27:00,493 --> 00:27:01,328
How pathetic.

340
00:27:01,411 --> 00:27:03,913
I'd expect nothing less from a half-wit.

341
00:27:03,997 --> 00:27:06,750
Cut her some slack. She half-succeeded.

342
00:27:06,833 --> 00:27:07,792
Well done, Chae-ni.

343
00:27:07,876 --> 00:27:10,170
Do you find this funny, Mr. Son?

344
00:27:10,670 --> 00:27:12,881
Would it be funny
if Cheong saw you get stuck?

345
00:27:12,964 --> 00:27:15,717
Hey, keep family out of this.

346
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:18,637
Then stop slacking off and practice.

347
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:22,057
I'm super scared that I'll end up
disappearing in front of Grandma.

348
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:24,267
She'd probably keel over from shock.

349
00:27:24,768 --> 00:27:25,852
That's not all.

350
00:27:25,935 --> 00:27:28,730
I'd be locked up forever
in the biggest hospital in Seoul.

351
00:27:29,230 --> 00:27:32,984
I'm more scared of Grandma finding out
than being carted off somewhere.

352
00:27:33,068 --> 00:27:35,028
I'm super desperate too.

353
00:27:35,528 --> 00:27:37,113
Do you know what my dream is?

354
00:27:37,656 --> 00:27:38,865
It's to be Uri Geller.

355
00:27:39,783 --> 00:27:40,950
Your dream

356
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:42,994
is to be a con artist?

357
00:27:43,078 --> 00:27:44,829
You're so clueless.

358
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:48,792
Uri Geller is a real psychic,
and he makes a ton of money.

359
00:27:51,127 --> 00:27:52,003
This.

360
00:27:52,796 --> 00:27:54,339
If I could gift one of these

361
00:27:54,422 --> 00:27:56,591
to each of Cheong's classmates,
I'd die happy.

362
00:27:58,760 --> 00:27:59,594
If I'm honest,

363
00:28:00,095 --> 00:28:03,098
like Mr. Son,
I also have something I'd like to do.

364
00:28:03,181 --> 00:28:04,015
What?

365
00:28:04,516 --> 00:28:05,975
Well, thanks to you,

366
00:28:06,059 --> 00:28:08,937
I had a pretty easy time in high school,

367
00:28:09,562 --> 00:28:11,856
but middle school was pretty rough.

368
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:15,026
I want to go and revisit every kid
who bullied me back then.

369
00:28:16,069 --> 00:28:18,738
Hey, Kang Ro-bin!

370
00:28:19,823 --> 00:28:21,866
Is the worm finally tuning?

371
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:24,994
What would you do to them?
Hurt them? Get revenge?

372
00:28:25,078 --> 00:28:26,830
No.

373
00:28:28,039 --> 00:28:28,998
I want to brag.

374
00:28:30,208 --> 00:28:31,793
That I've become really strong.

375
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:34,254
Typical Sappy Sap.

376
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:37,507
Can't you just go on
a brutal, bloodstained revenge spree?

377
00:28:37,590 --> 00:28:39,634
A guy like me get revenge? No way.

378
00:28:40,135 --> 00:28:42,095
Besides, in some ways,

379
00:28:42,178 --> 00:28:44,764
I sort of feel bad for my superpower.

380
00:28:45,265 --> 00:28:47,809
If it had gone to someone cooler,

381
00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:51,271
they would've used it in cool ways,
saved people, and all that.

382
00:28:51,771 --> 00:28:54,941
But it had to come
to someone useless like me.

383
00:28:55,024 --> 00:28:56,568
Now it's really useless.

384
00:28:58,153 --> 00:29:02,240
I recently saw the historical drama
500 Years of the Joseon Dynasty.

385
00:29:02,991 --> 00:29:04,367
They had these scapeghosts.

386
00:29:04,451 --> 00:29:05,785
Scapegoat, you mean.

387
00:29:05,869 --> 00:29:08,329
Anyway, they were basically goalies.

388
00:29:08,830 --> 00:29:12,292
They'd use their bodies
to block and absorb all the bad energy

389
00:29:12,792 --> 00:29:14,085
to protect the royal court.

390
00:29:14,169 --> 00:29:15,754
What's that got to do with me?

391
00:29:17,213 --> 00:29:20,300
Who else could handle the Royal Nightmare,

392
00:29:20,383 --> 00:29:21,634
Lady Trainwreck,

393
00:29:21,718 --> 00:29:24,304
and the curmudgeonly old lady
of Hearty House?

394
00:29:24,804 --> 00:29:26,598
Who would keep the peace in Haeseong?

395
00:29:29,601 --> 00:29:32,854
First, let's just try to figure out
how to use these abilities.

396
00:29:32,937 --> 00:29:36,399
He said we could avoid being carted off
and live normal, quiet lives.

397
00:29:36,483 --> 00:29:38,568
And once we get used to them,

398
00:29:39,611 --> 00:29:43,490
I'll get you some undies to wear
over your tights, like Superman.

399
00:29:43,990 --> 00:29:46,576
Really? And I get to pick out the design?

400
00:29:46,659 --> 00:29:47,744
I dare you.

401
00:29:51,956 --> 00:29:52,874
Hello?

402
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:54,626
Hey, Grandma.

403
00:29:55,126 --> 00:29:57,670
I'm busy with my public duties.
What is it now?

404
00:29:59,631 --> 00:30:00,548
Hello?

405
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:03,384
Hello? Grandma?

406
00:30:03,468 --> 00:30:05,553
Just tell me where you are.

407
00:30:05,637 --> 00:30:08,014
Do your public duties later
and come home now.

408
00:30:08,556 --> 00:30:09,432
Never mind.

409
00:30:09,516 --> 00:30:11,434
I'll pick you up. Where are you now?

410
00:30:11,518 --> 00:30:12,352
Hello?

411
00:30:12,852 --> 00:30:14,229
- Grandma.
- Hello?

412
00:30:14,312 --> 00:30:15,730
- I can hear--
- Eunie?

413
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:17,524
- Yes, Grandma--
- Eunie!

414
00:30:18,024 --> 00:30:18,858
Hello?

415
00:30:19,442 --> 00:30:21,236
- Hello? Grandma!
- Where are you?

416
00:30:23,279 --> 00:30:24,656
Hey, Gunie.

417
00:30:24,739 --> 00:30:27,784
Hurry back to the office
and find out where Eun Chae-ni is.

418
00:30:27,867 --> 00:30:28,701
Sorry?

419
00:30:29,536 --> 00:30:30,954
Right, okay.

420
00:30:34,290 --> 00:30:35,166
But, Ms. Kim,

421
00:30:36,209 --> 00:30:37,669
I guess you weren't aware

422
00:30:37,752 --> 00:30:40,421
that Eun Chae-ni had such an ability.

423
00:30:46,261 --> 00:30:47,262
Hello?

424
00:30:48,638 --> 00:30:50,139
Hey, Jun-mo.

425
00:30:53,893 --> 00:30:55,395
About Chae-ni.

426
00:30:55,478 --> 00:30:58,606
Looks like she's working hard
at the Civil Complaints Office.

427
00:31:00,567 --> 00:31:02,902
She hasn't budged an inch from City Hall.

428
00:31:03,862 --> 00:31:04,988
I see.

429
00:31:06,698 --> 00:31:07,991
And you're doing good?

430
00:31:08,074 --> 00:31:09,534
Of course.

431
00:31:10,034 --> 00:31:12,745
You'll be the first to know
if anything happens, Grandma.

432
00:31:15,039 --> 00:31:15,999
That's it.

433
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:19,752
Jun-mo has always called me Grandma.

434
00:31:20,336 --> 00:31:23,172
He's never called me "Ms. Kim."

435
00:31:26,634 --> 00:31:28,636
Damn, you caught me.

436
00:31:29,804 --> 00:31:32,515
It's always the little details
that give me away.

437
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:57,415
Whose daughter are you?

438
00:31:57,498 --> 00:31:59,167
Dr. Ha Won-do.

439
00:31:59,250 --> 00:32:00,460
He's my father.

440
00:32:01,377 --> 00:32:02,211
You

441
00:32:03,588 --> 00:32:05,506
call that man your father?

442
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:07,800
He's the only one who took us in.

443
00:32:08,593 --> 00:32:09,844
I guess I'm to blame.

444
00:32:11,095 --> 00:32:12,847
I failed to take care of you all.

445
00:32:16,267 --> 00:32:18,811
Don't say things you don't mean.

446
00:32:18,895 --> 00:32:21,439
We know you only saved the kids
without abilities.

447
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:28,780
You were afraid of the world
finding out we existed,

448
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,239
weren't you?

449
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:34,285
That's why you didn't save
the Wunderkinder.

450
00:32:34,369 --> 00:32:37,830
You just left us to die
in that burning lab.

451
00:32:39,457 --> 00:32:41,042
Did Ha Won-do tell you that?

452
00:32:41,876 --> 00:32:43,127
Child, that's not true.

453
00:32:43,211 --> 00:32:45,171
You only took the Child of Eternity.

454
00:32:47,632 --> 00:32:52,220
You guys only took the Child of Eternity,
who you needed, and as for the rest of us…

455
00:32:55,098 --> 00:32:56,099
you abandoned us.

456
00:32:57,684 --> 00:32:58,893
So that's it.

457
00:32:59,894 --> 00:33:00,979
The reason you're here.

458
00:33:04,607 --> 00:33:05,566
Where are they now?

459
00:33:05,650 --> 00:33:06,818
The child's dead.

460
00:33:08,403 --> 00:33:12,240
My sister's ability may not have worked
on you, but don't underestimate mine.

461
00:33:12,782 --> 00:33:16,202
I can make you experience

462
00:33:17,036 --> 00:33:17,996
hell on earth.

463
00:33:28,464 --> 00:33:29,424
Let me ask.

464
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:33,553
Do I look like I'm in a good place to you?

465
00:33:36,389 --> 00:33:39,559
After losing all those precious children,

466
00:33:40,226 --> 00:33:44,188
my own child was the one
who had to pay for that sin, not me.

467
00:33:48,985 --> 00:33:50,862
You needn't bother.

468
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:53,448
The past 20 years

469
00:33:53,948 --> 00:33:55,908
have already been hell on earth.

470
00:33:58,202 --> 00:34:00,163
Hello, we're here.

471
00:34:00,246 --> 00:34:01,914
- Hello.
- Please sit.

472
00:34:01,998 --> 00:34:04,250
- Welcome.
- Yes, hello.

473
00:34:04,333 --> 00:34:06,461
- Welcome.
- Whatever you want to eat.

474
00:34:07,003 --> 00:34:09,172
- Welcome.
- What should we eat?

475
00:34:13,718 --> 00:34:16,012
If that child really is dead,

476
00:34:17,430 --> 00:34:18,806
you'd better find the body.

477
00:34:20,850 --> 00:34:24,729
Or I'll show you true hell on earth.

478
00:34:31,986 --> 00:34:32,945
Did you hear that?

479
00:34:34,197 --> 00:34:35,156
You'd better go

480
00:34:36,199 --> 00:34:38,785
and find Chae-ni right now, Jun-mo.

481
00:34:42,622 --> 00:34:49,253
It is his will

482
00:34:49,337 --> 00:34:55,009
Forgive us our sins

483
00:34:55,551 --> 00:35:01,974
I will give my life

484
00:35:02,058 --> 00:35:07,313
To be saved

485
00:35:08,272 --> 00:35:14,195
A place where

486
00:35:14,278 --> 00:35:19,826
An endless paradise unfolds

487
00:35:20,326 --> 00:35:26,207
I will go to him

488
00:35:28,626 --> 00:35:30,336
Hey, look!

489
00:35:30,878 --> 00:35:34,132
Are we even sure there are rules?
I have no clue.

490
00:35:34,715 --> 00:35:36,926
Just sticking and unsticking willy-nilly.

491
00:35:37,009 --> 00:35:38,261
And the body part too.

492
00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:42,181
Sometimes it's my butt. Sometimes my arm.
It's completely random.

493
00:35:42,974 --> 00:35:45,643
There must be some kind of rule.
Think harder.

494
00:35:49,063 --> 00:35:50,523
You should think really hard.

495
00:35:50,606 --> 00:35:53,651
Don't you have the most to gain?
You'd have the strength of a tiger.

496
00:35:56,154 --> 00:35:56,988
Tears?

497
00:35:58,656 --> 00:35:59,907
I think I was crying.

498
00:36:06,247 --> 00:36:07,165
Tears.

499
00:36:07,248 --> 00:36:08,749
- He's crying.
- Try it now!

500
00:36:08,833 --> 00:36:10,001
Okay, straight punch.

501
00:36:10,084 --> 00:36:11,169
Okay, hi-yah!

502
00:36:11,252 --> 00:36:12,170
Okay.

503
00:36:13,588 --> 00:36:14,422
It didn't work?

504
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:16,716
Hey, more tears.

505
00:36:16,799 --> 00:36:17,717
Let's try again.

506
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:19,427
Put your back into it!

507
00:36:19,510 --> 00:36:20,344
Okay.

508
00:36:20,845 --> 00:36:21,762
Karate chop.

509
00:36:21,846 --> 00:36:23,764
- Hi-yah!
- Hi-yah!

510
00:36:25,975 --> 00:36:27,476
Go again. Hi-yah!

511
00:36:29,061 --> 00:36:30,354
I can't do it.

512
00:36:30,438 --> 00:36:32,857
Just hit it. What's a few broken fingers?

513
00:36:32,940 --> 00:36:33,816
It hurts.

514
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:35,651
Don't just stand like this. Do it!

515
00:36:35,735 --> 00:36:37,862
Okay, just once. Okay, go!

516
00:36:37,945 --> 00:36:39,030
One, two.

517
00:36:39,572 --> 00:36:40,698
It hurts too much.

518
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:43,868
Your tears are drying up.

519
00:36:43,951 --> 00:36:44,827
Go again?

520
00:36:44,911 --> 00:36:45,745
Hold on.

521
00:36:46,287 --> 00:36:47,413
It hurts.

522
00:36:48,873 --> 00:36:51,209
Hold your horses.

523
00:36:51,292 --> 00:36:54,462
I think I'm onto something.

524
00:36:54,962 --> 00:36:55,796
Run!

525
00:37:04,138 --> 00:37:05,932
Do I need to be out of breath?

526
00:37:07,767 --> 00:37:09,268
One, two!

527
00:37:09,977 --> 00:37:12,271
Hey, you punk! Why'd you hit me…

528
00:37:15,441 --> 00:37:17,693
Okay. Karate chop!

529
00:37:27,995 --> 00:37:29,413
I'll see you later.

530
00:37:33,334 --> 00:37:35,544
This is the end of my patrol area.

531
00:37:35,628 --> 00:37:37,296
This field is the last stop.

532
00:37:37,380 --> 00:37:38,214
I see.

533
00:37:40,091 --> 00:37:42,426
So this will be the last stop.

534
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:46,222
Thank you for your help.

535
00:37:46,305 --> 00:37:48,516
I think I can take it from here.

536
00:37:48,599 --> 00:37:49,517
That's all right.

537
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:52,979
I was told that we should see
the clean-up through to the end.

538
00:37:54,021 --> 00:37:54,939
Who said that?

539
00:37:55,022 --> 00:37:58,651
Who else?
Our very own shepherd, Kim Pal-ho.

540
00:38:01,862 --> 00:38:04,407
And it seems you have blind faith
in your shepherd.

541
00:38:05,783 --> 00:38:06,617
No.

542
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:09,287
To believe or not to believe

543
00:38:09,370 --> 00:38:12,081
involves human will, does it not?

544
00:38:12,164 --> 00:38:15,126
We do not believe. We know.

545
00:38:17,461 --> 00:38:19,922
We are aware of the fact

546
00:38:20,423 --> 00:38:22,258
that the apocalypse is near.

547
00:38:23,801 --> 00:38:25,803
"The apocalypse will come."

548
00:38:25,886 --> 00:38:28,347
"There is no escaping that fact."

549
00:38:29,015 --> 00:38:33,269
"Everyone dies.
There is no escaping that fact."

550
00:38:33,853 --> 00:38:34,895
How are they different?

551
00:38:35,855 --> 00:38:37,064
The difference

552
00:38:37,148 --> 00:38:42,028
is that our shepherd knows when, where,
and how the apocalypse will happen.

553
00:38:42,111 --> 00:38:44,488
What's the point of
knowing about the apocalypse

554
00:38:44,989 --> 00:38:46,490
if you can't avoid it?

555
00:38:47,742 --> 00:38:49,952
That's right. It cannot be avoided.

556
00:38:50,036 --> 00:38:51,912
Not by foolish humans.

557
00:38:51,996 --> 00:38:55,541
But the Church of Eternal Salvation
is different.

558
00:38:55,624 --> 00:38:56,959
We can be saved.

559
00:39:00,671 --> 00:39:04,050
We have witnessed miracles
with our own two eyes.

560
00:39:04,133 --> 00:39:05,968
And we know that such miracles

561
00:39:06,510 --> 00:39:09,930
will be granted to us
at the moment of the apocalypse.

562
00:39:12,058 --> 00:39:14,810
Whatever you saw wasn't a miracle, but…

563
00:39:33,954 --> 00:39:35,831
Lord, are you with us?

564
00:39:37,166 --> 00:39:39,335
My Lord!

565
00:39:40,961 --> 00:39:43,589
My Lord! Please forgive us our sins.

566
00:39:43,672 --> 00:39:44,840
Please save us.

567
00:39:44,924 --> 00:39:48,969
Save all our believers
in the midst of the apocalypse!

568
00:39:49,470 --> 00:39:50,429
Are you here?

569
00:39:50,513 --> 00:39:52,056
Please forgive my sins.

570
00:39:52,139 --> 00:39:56,560
I am ready to give my life for you!

571
00:39:59,146 --> 00:40:01,774
Shepherd Kim Pal-ho asked me
to pass on a message.

572
00:40:01,857 --> 00:40:04,819
Number 3972,
your apocalypse shall take place

573
00:40:04,902 --> 00:40:06,362
right here, today,

574
00:40:06,445 --> 00:40:08,364
and there shall be no mercy.

575
00:41:40,789 --> 00:41:44,293
You laughed earlier, didn't you?
When he said "Shepherd Kim Pal-ho."

576
00:41:46,921 --> 00:41:48,297
What are you talking about?

577
00:41:48,797 --> 00:41:49,715
You crazy bastard!

578
00:42:01,727 --> 00:42:05,231
Didn't you know that disbelief
in the shepherd gets you a ticket to hell?

579
00:42:15,908 --> 00:42:17,868
Hey, Kang Ro-bin, you bastard!

580
00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:20,204
How dare you throw an adult up here!

581
00:42:20,871 --> 00:42:24,375
I did throw you, but you were the one
who got yourself stuck up there.

582
00:42:24,458 --> 00:42:25,417
Why, you…

583
00:42:26,502 --> 00:42:28,420
I ran so hard that I'm out of breath,

584
00:42:28,504 --> 00:42:30,506
so why isn't my heart racing?

585
00:42:30,589 --> 00:42:31,465
This is weird.

586
00:42:33,300 --> 00:42:35,177
Maybe you have to decide where to go.

587
00:42:35,261 --> 00:42:37,638
But there's nowhere
I want to go right now.

588
00:42:39,598 --> 00:42:43,435
I have to figure this out
so I can tell Master and show off.

589
00:42:47,314 --> 00:42:50,025
I'm just dying to show off!

590
00:42:52,152 --> 00:42:53,362
Chae-ni!

591
00:42:56,657 --> 00:42:57,825
No matter what,

592
00:42:59,076 --> 00:43:00,786
I will become Uri Geller.

593
00:43:01,996 --> 00:43:04,582
But why won't I get off?

594
00:43:11,505 --> 00:43:12,840
Pretty awesome!

595
00:43:13,507 --> 00:43:16,927
Hey, Master! I did it.

596
00:43:17,011 --> 00:43:19,930
I thought hard and focused like you said,
and I ended up--

597
00:43:25,561 --> 00:43:26,604
Run.

598
00:43:35,654 --> 00:43:37,823
- What the heck?
- Eun Chae-ni!

599
00:43:38,490 --> 00:43:39,992
Where's Master?

600
00:43:40,075 --> 00:43:41,327
It's just you. What is it?

601
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:45,080
Master is in danger!

602
00:43:45,164 --> 00:43:47,875
You have to give
the who, what, when, where, why, and how.

603
00:43:47,958 --> 00:43:50,294
You can't just say he's in danger
and expect us to…

604
00:43:50,377 --> 00:43:51,920
Who am I even talking to?

605
00:43:52,421 --> 00:43:54,673
All the blood in my body
is rushing to my head.

606
00:43:54,757 --> 00:43:55,883
Someone get me down.

607
00:43:58,177 --> 00:43:59,762
What?

608
00:44:02,890 --> 00:44:04,141
What is that?

609
00:44:04,224 --> 00:44:05,476
Chae-ni! No!

610
00:44:06,018 --> 00:44:07,061
Get up.

611
00:44:10,731 --> 00:44:11,982
Chae-ni!

612
00:44:14,193 --> 00:44:16,195
Chae-ni!

613
00:44:17,321 --> 00:44:18,364
Master!

614
00:44:24,119 --> 00:44:25,371
Master.

615
00:44:27,247 --> 00:44:29,083
Now you've brought Kang Ro-bin too?

616
00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:30,000
Go back, now!

617
00:44:30,084 --> 00:44:31,669
We have to go together!

618
00:44:32,711 --> 00:44:33,545
Hey, Kang Ro-bin!

619
00:44:40,386 --> 00:44:41,470
Oh no!

620
00:44:41,553 --> 00:44:42,471
Focus.

621
00:44:48,227 --> 00:44:49,103
What are you doing?

622
00:44:49,186 --> 00:44:51,939
Hey, don't talk to me!
Why isn't it working?

623
00:44:52,523 --> 00:44:53,357
Let's go!

624
00:45:23,512 --> 00:45:25,180
What is this?

625
00:45:27,057 --> 00:45:28,058
He's a Wunderkinder.

626
00:45:39,987 --> 00:45:40,863
Hurry, go back.

627
00:45:40,946 --> 00:45:44,032
I'm dying to go back too.

628
00:45:46,034 --> 00:45:47,578
Chae-ni, what do we do?

629
00:45:47,661 --> 00:45:49,747
It looks like we're going to die here!

630
00:45:49,830 --> 00:45:51,832
Get off me and stop whining!

631
00:45:51,915 --> 00:45:52,958
Stop freeloading,

632
00:45:53,041 --> 00:45:56,712
and think of something
that'll actually help us yourself!

633
00:46:48,055 --> 00:46:49,181
No!

634
00:47:43,694 --> 00:47:46,113
Chae-ni! Did you see that?

635
00:47:46,655 --> 00:47:47,781
I just…

636
00:47:49,199 --> 00:47:50,492
Chae-ni!

637
00:47:51,660 --> 00:47:52,744
Where did Chae-ni…

638
00:47:53,370 --> 00:47:54,204
Chae-ni!

639
00:47:56,039 --> 00:47:57,082
Chae-ni!

640
00:48:21,148 --> 00:48:22,232
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

641
00:48:23,734 --> 00:48:24,610
Ms. Chae-ni!

642
00:48:25,569 --> 00:48:26,820
Are you okay?

643
00:48:27,321 --> 00:48:28,322
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

644
00:48:32,534 --> 00:48:33,827
This time,

645
00:48:35,162 --> 00:48:37,414
I actually did it.

646
00:48:40,834 --> 00:48:43,587
It's the northern lights.

647
00:49:01,480 --> 00:49:03,065
It's my first time

648
00:49:04,191 --> 00:49:06,443
being outside of Haeseong.

649
00:49:16,745 --> 00:49:18,246
It's beautiful.

650
00:49:30,509 --> 00:49:31,343
Hey.

651
00:49:32,010 --> 00:49:32,844
Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

652
00:49:34,012 --> 00:49:34,846
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

653
00:49:35,347 --> 00:49:36,306
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

654
00:49:54,324 --> 00:49:56,618
Chae-ni!

655
00:49:57,119 --> 00:49:58,578
Eun Chae-ni!

656
00:49:59,079 --> 00:50:02,249
How could you leave me here all alone?

657
00:50:06,545 --> 00:50:07,963
You scared me.

658
00:50:08,463 --> 00:50:10,632
You could've made some noise or something.

659
00:50:10,716 --> 00:50:11,883
And who are you?

660
00:50:13,176 --> 00:50:14,094
Another defective?

661
00:50:16,013 --> 00:50:16,930
Me?

662
00:50:17,514 --> 00:50:18,765
Who said I defected?

663
00:50:23,061 --> 00:50:27,566
If you're a Wunderkinder, that means
you also have a superpower, doesn't it?

664
00:50:32,988 --> 00:50:34,573
Why are you doing that?

665
00:51:13,445 --> 00:51:14,571
What are you doing?

666
00:51:16,865 --> 00:51:17,783
What are you?

667
00:51:18,366 --> 00:51:19,451
I'm Kang Ro-bin.

668
00:51:22,037 --> 00:51:24,372
Wait, why do you keep clapping?

669
00:51:28,460 --> 00:51:29,669
Should I be copying him?

670
00:51:32,005 --> 00:51:32,839
Boom pow?

671
00:51:35,509 --> 00:51:36,676
Boom boom pow!

672
00:51:39,554 --> 00:51:41,014
Boom boom pow!

673
00:51:41,098 --> 00:51:42,682
Boom boom pow!

674
00:51:42,766 --> 00:51:44,768
Boom boom pow!

675
00:51:44,851 --> 00:51:47,562
Boom boom pow! Is this it? Boom boom pow!

676
00:51:48,980 --> 00:51:50,148
Pow!

677
00:51:52,692 --> 00:51:54,319
This is it, right? Boom boom pow!

678
00:51:54,402 --> 00:51:56,238
Boom boom pow!

679
00:51:56,321 --> 00:51:57,405
Ha, ha, pow!

680
00:51:59,407 --> 00:52:04,037
I recently saw the historical drama
500 Years of the Joseon Dynasty.

681
00:52:04,663 --> 00:52:06,456
They had scapeghosts.

682
00:52:06,957 --> 00:52:08,708
Scapegoat, you mean.

683
00:52:08,792 --> 00:52:11,128
Anyway, they were basically goalies.

684
00:52:11,878 --> 00:52:15,715
They'd use their bodies
to block and absorb all the bad energy

685
00:52:15,799 --> 00:52:17,592
to protect the royal court.

686
00:52:36,736 --> 00:52:38,488
Peek-a-boo! Wait, not peek-a-boo.

687
00:52:38,572 --> 00:52:41,032
First of all,
I'm glad you're not too surprised.

688
00:52:41,116 --> 00:52:42,409
Deary me, this is…

689
00:52:42,492 --> 00:52:44,911
Right, I am Son Gyeong--

690
00:52:48,373 --> 00:52:49,833
Just a second.

691
00:52:50,375 --> 00:52:51,585
My head's spinning.

692
00:52:54,212 --> 00:52:55,088
I'm good now.

693
00:52:56,506 --> 00:52:59,342
You were… stuck up there?

694
00:53:00,552 --> 00:53:03,096
No. What do you mean "stuck"?

695
00:53:03,680 --> 00:53:06,391
I performed some magic tricks
for a talent show,

696
00:53:06,474 --> 00:53:07,601
and the kids…

697
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:10,395
I wonder where the kids went…

698
00:53:13,356 --> 00:53:14,232
Not again…

699
00:53:18,695 --> 00:53:21,072
Mister, what are you doing right now?

700
00:53:23,533 --> 00:53:24,576
Hold on.

701
00:53:27,078 --> 00:53:28,830
I just…

702
00:53:31,958 --> 00:53:34,961
By the way, where is Chae-ni right now?

703
00:58:03,855 --> 00:58:08,860
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi
